DURBAN–A 45-year-old taxi owner was murdered in front of his family on Saturday in Verulam. Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele, who said that the man was at home with his family when the gunmen arrived.  “It is alleged that the deceased male, 45, was with his children's mother when two unknown males came and one shot him dead without saying a word. The deceased sustained three gunshot wounds to his head and one in the stomach.” Mbele said that, according to the witness, the deceased had one taxi operating at Kwandengezi and one at Inanda.  “The information at the scene revealed that there were four suspects but only two went inside whilst one remained in the white BMW latest series 320i with GP registration and the other was on the other side of the house.” Mbele added that police were investigating the murder.  “The suspects are not known at this stage, three empty cartridges of a pistol and one projectile were found at the scene.” Reaction Unit South Africa spokesperson Prem Balram said its officers were called out to the housing complex.  “On arrival, it was established that the deceased was in a bedroom with his partner and two sons on the upper level of the home. Two men entered the residence and shot the taxi boss multiple times in the presence of his family before they fled the scene.” THE MERCURY